title: Zetela annectens
text:
Zetela annectens is a <a href="species">species</a> of <a href="sea%20snail">sea snail</a>, a marine <a href="gastropod">gastropod</a> <a href="mollusk">mollusk</a> in the <a href="family%20%28biology%29">family</a> <a href="Solariellidae">Solariellidae</a>, the top snails.
Distribution.
This marine species is <a href="endemic">endemic</a> to New Zealand and occurs off the <a href="Great%20Barrier%20Island">Great Barrier Island</a> at depths between 486 m and 655 m.
